A 78-YEAR-OLD lady was attacked by a dog that set upon her Jack Russell.&nbsp;Police said the woman and her dog were in Howe Road, Kilsyth, yesterday when they were attacked by a Staffordshire Bull Terrier.It is understood the dog was pulled away by two Good Samaritans who witnessed the incident.Police are appealing for information.They said the attack occurred at 2pm.It is not known how badly injured the pensioner or her dog are. Both required medical treatment.